<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1009] LogByteSizeMergePolicy over-merges with autoCommit=false and documents with term vectors and/or stored fields</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1009</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Mark Miller noticed this slowdown (see details in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-994&quot; title=&quot;Change defaults in IndexWriter to maximize &amp;quot;out of the box&amp;quot; performance&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-994&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) in his&lt;br/&gt;
app.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happens because in SegmentInfo.sizeInBytes(), we just run through&lt;br/&gt;
all files associated with that segment, summing up their byte sizes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But in the case of shared doc stores (which happens when&lt;br/&gt;
autoCommit=false), this is not quite correct because those files are&lt;br/&gt;
shared across multiple segments.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I plan to fix sizeInBytes() to not include the size of the doc stores&lt;br/&gt;
when they are shared.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
